Class MusicLibrary

  • java.lang.Object
    • MusicLibrary

  • public class MusicLibrary
extends java.lang.Object

    Array Tools

    The Music Library program implements an application that can manipulate pitches and durations to form long arrays of playable music. Chords and harmonics can be played. Volume changes and other effects can be implemented onto pieces of music as well.

    12/22/17

      • sinstuff

        public static double[] sinstuff​(double duration,
                                double hz)
        This method is used to turn a frequency into a double array, containing a single note with a given duration.
        Parameters:
        duration - The number of seconds the note will play
        hz - The frequency of the notes
        Returns:
        a An array that holds the sin graph that can be played using StdAudio

      • harmonics

        public static double[] harmonics​(int pitch,
                                 double duration)
        This method is used to turn a pitch into a double array, containing a harmonic with a given duration. It uses the sinstuff method to generate two arrays of a single note each: one an octave higher and another an octave lower than the inputted pitch. These two arrays are then layered to form a harmonic.
        Parameters:
        duration - The number of seconds the harmonic will play
        pitch - The root pitch of the harmonic
        Returns:
        a An array that holds the sin graph of a harmonic that can be played using StdAudio

      • majorChord

        public static double[] majorChord​(int pitch,
                                  double duration)
        This method is used to turn a pitch into a double array, containing a major chord with a given duration. It uses the sinstuff method to generate three arrays of a single note each: the inputted pitch (root note), the major third, and the perfect fifth. These arrays are then layered to form a major chord.
        Parameters:
        duration - The number of seconds the major chord will play
        pitch - The root pitch of the chord
        Returns:
        a An array that holds the sin graph of a major chord that can be played using StdAudio

It uses the sinstuff method to generate three arrays of a single note each: the inputted pitch (root note), the minor third, and the perfect fifth. These arrays are then layered to form a minor chord.
        Parameters:

        pitch - The root pitch of the chord
        Returns:
        a An array that holds the sin graph of a minor chord that can be played using StdAudio

      • echo

        public static double[] echo​(double[] a,
                            double secs,
                            int repetition)
        This method repeats a tone based on a time interval and a number of repitions. The volume will always start from 1, its maximum and work its way down to 0.
        Parameters:
        a - The array to be manipulated
        secs - The number of seconds the music should fade out for
        repetition - The number of times the tone should repeat
        Returns:
        finalA The final array
